text:
This coffeeshop is quite cool and airy especially the outside sitting area. The tze char here is amazing. The salted fish fried rice is so flavourful and full of wok hei. It also comes with 4 pieces of medium size prawns and cost $6 which is very reasonable. The beef hor fun also has good wok hei and the sauce is really yummy. Beef slices are tender and nice and the hor fun is thin and soft. My only wish is that it had more vegetables but it is definitely one of the best beef hor fun.
Service is OK.  It takes some time for the dishes to come out but is definitely worth the wait.
Clean and brightly lighted coffeeshop. Tried a few stalls and I like how they were able to customize the dish to my preference. Food price is cheap and reasonable!
Do try their curry fishhead tze char stall, food is good!! Curry is thick and delicious, so are their other dishes :)

Like the clean environment. Food options including mala, ban mian, western, zhi char, bak kut teh, and etc. The kopi stall also sells dim sum.
The food is good while price also reasonable. My zhi char order today cost $22 including 1 soup 1 egg 1 vege and 1 rice.

was here for brunch (about 2pm)
pretty windy as coffee shop owner installed many ceiling fans
I had Horfun mix $5.00
& breakfast set $3.50
ALL tasted so nice & me paid ONLY $8.50
with this price = hard to find!
